		<li id="comment-1069" class="comment byuser comment-author-parfles bypostauthor odd alt depth-2">
			<article id="div-comment-1069" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/?s=56&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/?s=112&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-56 photo avatar-default' height='56' width='56' />						<b class="fn">parfles</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="http://localhost:8888/microfiction.co.za/2010/12/26/hot/#comment-1069">
							<time datetime="2010-12-28T11:45:16+00:00">
								December 28, 2010 at 11:45 am							</time>
						</a>
											</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Ah, Agnes definitely came out a little spooky &#8211; a genius inventor child somehow turns out that way in my head.</p>
<p>I say pshaw! to historical register, as it involves research and suchlike 😉 No, seriously, I did not have this in my head as the Victorian steampunk convention &#8211; this is somewhere, somewhen, in a parallel universe not so far away, and so a mixture of modern and victorian language was fine in my head. If anything, I tried to make things sound slightly off to make the place sound slightly different to our reality.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='http://localhost:8888/microfiction.co.za/2010/12/26/hot/?replytocom=1069#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm( "div-comment-1069", "1069", "respond", "625" )' aria-label='Reply to parfles'>Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
